              They were feared to have brought back a virus from space, but there was no such issue. Although, they did have to quarantine just in case.
            </p>
            <% end %>
          </td>
          <td>
            <fieldset style="border-style: none;" name="5.1">
              <label for="5.1.true">.</label>
              <input type="radio" name="5.1" id="5.1.true" value="true">
              <label for="5.1.false">-</label>
              <input type="radio" name="5.1" id="5.1.false" value="false">
            </fieldset>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>2.</td>
          <td>
            <p>
              The famous gothic horror Dracula was written by Bram Stoker while the author was in Quarantine
            </p>
            <% if answers['5.2'] %>
            <p class="fun_fact">
              False! But Frankenstein was when Mary Shelley was isolating during a cholera epidemic.
            </p>
            <% end %>
          </td>
          <td>
            <fieldset style="border-style: none;" name="5.2">
              <label for="5.2.true">.</label>
              <input type="radio" name="5.2" id="5.2.true" value="true">
              <label for="5.2.false">-</label>
              <input type="radio" name="5.2" id="5.2.false" value="false">
            </fieldset>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>3.</td>
          <td>
            <p>
              Isaac Newton changed our understanding of the universe while in isolation.
            </p>
            <% if answers['5.3'] %>
            <p class="fun_fact">
               When the Great Plague of London ravaged London Isaac Newton retreated to his family's farm at Woolsthorpe Manor. He studied optics and showed that white light is composed of all components of the spectrum, leading to the inception of astronomical spectroscopy.  And all you’re doing is this stupid  challenge.
            </p>
            <% end %>
          </td>
          <td>
            <fieldset style="border-style: none;" name="5.3">
              <label for="5.3.true">.</label>
              <input type="radio" name="5.3" id="5.3.true" value="true">
              <label for="5.3.false">-</label>
              <input type="radio" name="5.3" id="5.3.false" value="false">
            </fieldset>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <input class="submit" type="submit" value="Check Answers">
    </form>
  </div>
</body>
<script>
  let query = window.location.search
  query = query.replace("?", "")
  let params = query.split("&");
  params = params.map(p => p.replace("=", "."))
  params.forEach((p) => {
    let el = document.getElementById(p)
    el.click()
  })
</script>
</html>
